<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
 <head>
  
  <title>HTML Styles</title>
 </head>
 <body style="background-color:white";>
  <h1 style="font-size:20px">This is Heading 1</h1>
  <p>The CSS background-color property defines the background color for an HTML element.</p>

  <h1 style="background-color:powderblue";>Heading 1</h1> <!-----to provide background color for h1--->
  <p style="background-color:green">This is a paragraph</p> <!-----to provide background color for p--->

  <h2 style="color:green">Heading 2</h2> <!---to set the text color of heading---->
  <p style="color:pink">paragraph 1</p>  <!---to set the text color of paragraph---->

 </body>
</html>
